      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation experiments conducted on geometry and at conditions representative of the COU.",
      "rationale": "Validation experiments used the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump geometry, which is the same geometry used in the COU tolerance study. Operating conditions span the clinical CPB envelope. Blood analogue properties matched to clinical haematocrit range. Validation activities are directly relevant to the COU. Level 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative convergence demonstrated; residuals reduced to acceptable levels for all equations.",
      "rationale": "All simulations converged to residuals below 1×10⁻⁵ for continuity and momentum equations and 1×10⁻⁶ for turbulence scalars. Mass imbalance across inlet/outlet boundaries less than 0.01%. Convergence monitored via pressure head and torque monitors stabilising to less than 0.1% change over final 500 iterations. Level 1 requirement met."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Simulation inputs and boundary conditions independently reviewed by a second analyst.",
      "rationale": "All boundary condition settings, material properties, and solver settings were independently reviewed by a second CFD analyst prior to production runs. Discrepancies identified during review were corrected before final simulation execution. Review records archived in project quality file. Level 1 requirement met."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Turbulence model and hemolysis model selections justified with reference to published validation evidence for rotating blood-contacting devices.",
      "rationale": "SST k-ω turbulence model selected based on published benchmark studies for centrifugal blood pumps (Hariharan et al. 2011, Fraser et al. 2012) demonstrating superior near-wall accuracy over standard k-ε. Giersiepen power-law hemolysis model applied with Lagrangian particle tracking; model limitations acknowledged. Steady-state MRF approach validated against transient sliding-mesh results showing <3% difference in RH at design point. Level 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
